==English==

===Etymology===
From the classical Greek transliterated as "Diabainein" -"To pass through" it is from the participle of this verb and therefore means passing through. This refers to the excessive amounts of urine produced by sufferers (see below).

===Noun===
'''diabetes'''
#A disease which is attended with a persistent, excessive discharge of urine. Most frequently the urine is not only increased in quantity, but contains saccharine matter. Untreated, the disease leads to an earlier death.   
#[[Diabetes mellitus]].

